Heat the oven to 350 degrees and line a couple of baking sheets with parchment. Using a 1Â½-tablespoon cookie scoop (or two spoons) and working one at a time, scoop out 1Â½-inch/29-gram rounds and coat them in @powdered sugar{92 grams}. Place them a couple of inches apart on the baking sheets and bake until crinkled and no longer wet-looking on top, 15 to 17 minutes. Let cool completely on the pan before eating.

