Tips

To make ahead, prepare cookies up through Step 2, then scoop out 1Â½-tablespoon rounds and set them in a single layer in a resealable container. Freeze the dough, covered, for up to 1 month. When ready to bake, coat frozen dough balls in powdered sugar and bake, adding 1 to 2 minutes as needed. When measuring flour, be sure to scoop it into the measuring cup, then level it using the back of a butter knife.

